  section#details1
    .intro.row
      .col-md-6.col-md-offset-3.col-xs-12
        h2 What is Waigo?
        :markdown
          Waigo is a low-level framework for building scalable web applications in Node.js. Waigo combines **es6 generators**
          with a **flexible module loading** mechanism and **configurable architecture** to enable you to build the application 
          you need, without getting in your way.
    .features.row
      .col-md-4
        i.glyphicon.glyphicon-road
        h3 Next-generation
        :markdown
          Waigo builds on [Koa](http://koajs.com), the ES6 successor to 
          Express. Callback hell is eliminated and error handling is 
          simplified thanks to *Promises* and *Generators*.
      .col-md-4
        i.glyphicon.glyphicon-wrench
        h3 Customizable
        :markdown
          Almost every module file within the core framework can be 
          [overridden](/guide.html#extend-and-override), allowing you to customise the behaviour of the framework 
          to suit your needs. It gets out of your way when you need it to.
      .col-md-4
        i.glyphicon.glyphicon-compressed
        h3 Lean machine
        :markdown
          The core framework is small and gives you access to the underlying 
          Koa objects. You can also use your preferred [back-end storage](/guide.html#database-and-models)
          and front-end UI frameworks.
    .features.row
      .col-md-4
        i.glyphicon.glyphicon-phone
        h3 REST APIs
        :markdown
          With [output formats](/guide.html#views-and-output-formats)  it's easy 
          to re-use your controllers to serve a REST API to your single-page 
          and mobile apps. 
      .col-md-4
        i.glyphicon.glyphicon-align-justify
        h3 Command-line power
        :markdown
          The [command-line client](#/guide.html#command-line) makes it 
          really easy to start using Waigo. The best part is you can extend 
          it with your own commands relevant to your application.
      .col-md-4
        i.glyphicon.glyphicon-share
        h3 Plugins
        :markdown
          Have an override or feature you'd like to share? Just bundle it 
          up as a [plugin](/guide.html#plugin). And since plugins are just NPM 
          modules they're easy to distribute and use.

  section#details2
    h2 Quick start
    .row
      .col-md-6
        pre
          code.language-bash
            $ npm install -g waigo
            $ waigo init
            $ ./start-app.js
      .col-md-6
        :markdown 
          If you visit `http://localhost:3000` in your browser you should see 
          some welcome text.

          You can now start adding controllers and models and develop your 
          application.


